catalog.title: Stochastic Processes
catalog.description: Stochastic processes describe the dynamics of systems that evolve in time acceding to probabilistic laws, rather than deterministic laws. We particularly study Markov processes, which have the property that the future only depends on the present, not on the past. Topics to be covered are discrete Markov chains, Poisson processes, continuous Markov chains, Brownian motion, among others. The course emphasizes the mathematical formulation of concepts as well as applications and computations. Measure theory is not employed.

catalog.title: Data-Oriented Computing II
catalog.description: The course will introduce students to state-of-the-art data-analysis methodology in which mathematics plays a crucial role. Topics that will be covered may include page rank, community detection, spectral clustering, manifold learning, persistent homology, tensor decompositions, and deep learning. Students will be required to complete both hand-written and Python-based coding assignments.
